Checklist mapping for the current web prototype

Inputs used by implemented checks:
- TOC XML / e-rights XML
- Paper PDF
- HotCRP ACM settings HTML
- Track review state saved locally by the app

Checklist items displayed on the webpage

1. PDF title matches metadata
   Maps to original supported item 1: Check that the paper title in the PDF matches the title in the XML/e-rights metadata.

2. PDF author list matches metadata
   Maps to original supported item 2: Check that the author list in the PDF matches the author list in the XML/e-rights metadata.

3. PDF affiliations match metadata
   Maps to original supported item 3: Check that author affiliations in the PDF match the affiliations in the XML/e-rights metadata where affiliation text can be extracted from the PDF.

4. All author emails in metadata appear in the PDF
   Maps to original supported items 4 and 5: Check that author email addresses in the PDF match the email addresses in the XML/e-rights metadata; check that all author email addresses from the XML/e-rights metadata appear in the camera-ready PDF.

5. All authors have ORCID in metadata
   Maps to original supported item 6: Check whether every author in the XML/e-rights metadata has an ORCID value.

6. ACM keywords added on HotCRP
   Maps to original supported item 7: Check whether ACM keywords are missing on the HotCRP page, using HotCRP ACM proceeding warnings.

7. ACM Computing Classification added on HotCRP
   Maps to original supported item 8: Check whether ACM Computing Classification / CCS is missing on the HotCRP page, using HotCRP ACM proceeding warnings.

8. References added on HotCRP
   Maps to original supported item 9: Check whether references are missing on the HotCRP page, using HotCRP ACM proceeding warnings.

9. Source files submitted
   Maps to original supported item 10: Check whether source files were submitted for the camera-ready version, using HotCRP ACM settings HTML source-file links.

10. Other issues
    Maps to original supported item 11: Check HotCRP ACM proceeding warnings and errors for each paper, including missing fonts, bad fonts, missing ACM metadata, missing references, and other proceeding messages shown in the HTML.

11. PDF copyright information includes ISBN
    Maps to the checklist requirement that copyright/license information is present and consistent. This implementation checks that PDF copyright/license text and an ISBN marker are present in extracted PDF text.

12. Page count available and locally consistent
    Maps to original supported items 13 and 21: Check the page count recorded in the HotCRP ACM settings HTML; check PDF-level properties where the backend supports them.

13. Paper PDF provided
    App-specific intake check: confirms the ZIP contains a matching local paper PDF.

14. PDF has no visible page numbers
    Maps to the checklist requirement that final papers should not include page numbers.

15. Latest ACM template used
    Maps to original supported item 16: Check whether the PDF appears to use ACM formatting/template cues. This remains a chair-review item in the prototype.

16. Authors stacked individually
    Maps to original supported item 17: Check whether authors appear to be stacked individually in the PDF according to ACM interim layout guidance. This remains a chair-review item in the prototype.

17. Last page balanced
    Maps to original supported item 18: Check whether the last page appears visually balanced. This remains a chair-review item in the prototype.

18. Track-specific page limit followed
    Maps to original supported item 14: Check whether the PDF page count follows the configured page limit for the paper type or track. This remains a chair-review item until authoritative track/page-limit rules are configured.
